credit.credit-words: Words and music by Paul Simon

direction-type.words:
NARRATOR: In the following selection of songs we will follow the progress of a young man, as seen through the eyes of Paul Simon in his days as one of the duo Simon & Garfunkel.
As with many young people, our hero leaves home seeking fame and fortune, to what effect you may determine from our first song...

NARRATOR:
The trials and tribulations of making his way in the world have left our hero depressed and disillusioned, and wondering what it's all about...
NARRATOR: At last our young man decides to cut his losses, and return home.
NARRATOR: So our adventurer arrives home, only to find that it has its own set of problems..
NARRATOR: Finally, having sorted out his love life, its now time for our young man to sit back, relax, and have beer!
